# ─── Whitelist: this repo tracks only the customization toolkit ───────
# Strategy: ignore EVERYTHING, then re-include just the toolkit folders
# and a short list of root files. Anything else — any private deck, asset
# folder, script, or new root file, now or in the future — is ignored by
# default and will not be committed.

# Ignore every top-level entry...
/*

# ...re-include the toolkit: the shared core + the look variants...
!/core/
!/variants/

# ...and these root files only.
!/.gitignore
!/CLAUDE.md
!/package.json
!/pnpm-lock.yaml
!/pnpm-workspace.yaml
!/README.md

# Decks live one-per-folder under decks/<name>/ (slides.md + pages/ + public/ + data/).
# Re-include the dir (so git descends), ignore its contents, then keep only the two
# decks that ship with the toolkit: the starter template and the tutorial. Every other
# deck — private presentations — stays ignored automatically.
!/decks/
/decks/*
!/decks/template/
!/decks/tutorial/

# Inside the tutorial deck, track only the two demo assets out of public/
# (same three-step, then pick the files).
/decks/tutorial/public/*
!/decks/tutorial/public/layout-demo.svg
!/decks/tutorial/public/slidev-logo.png

# The deploy script + its helpers (tracked so anyone with the repo can publish); other
# scripts (figure pipelines, scratch tools) stay ignored — same three-step.
!/scripts/
/scripts/*
!/scripts/deploy.sh
!/scripts/export-pdf.mjs

# Junk to keep out even inside the tracked folders above (node_modules appears
# inside core/ and variants/ now that they are pnpm workspace packages).
node_modules/
dist/
.vite-inspect/
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.log

# Track the git-github deck (opted in — public in this repo).
!/decks/git-github/
